<section id="command-screencolor">
    <title>SCREENCOLOR</title>
<indexterm><primary>SCREENCOLOR</primary></indexterm>

<variablelist>

<varlistentry><term>Synopsis</term>
<listitem>
<synopsis><command>SCREENCOLOR</command>
<command>SCREENCOLOUR</command></synopsis>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>

<varlistentry><term>Description</term>
<listitem>
<para>
Outputs screen color information.
This is either a color index (a number from 0 - 15), or a list containing [red green blue] intensities, depending on how the screen color was set.
</para>

</listitem>
</varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term>Example</term>
<listitem>
<programlisting><userinput>SETSCREENCOLOR [100 200 50]
SHOW SCREENCOLOR</userinput>
[100 200 50]
</programlisting>

<programlisting><userinput>SETSCREENCOLOR 2
SHOW SCREENCOLOR</userinput>
2</programlisting>
</listitem>
</varlistentry>
</variablelist>

</section>
